comments.LineComment: | Property-based tests for 3D math: Vec3, Mat4, Quat

value.value: addition is commutative: a + b = b + a
lerp at t=0 returns first vector
lerp at t=1 returns second vector
rotation X composition: Rx(a) * Rx(b) = Rx(a+b)
determinant of scale matrix is product of scales
invert of scale: S * S^-1 = I
multiply identity is identity: q * I = q
multiply by inverse gives identity: q * q^-1 = I
fromEuler -> toEuler roundtrip in stable range
gimbal lock does not produce NaN
slerp at t=0 returns first quaternion
slerp at t=1 returns second quaternion
rotateVec3 by identity returns original vector
90 rotation around Z maps X to Y
fromArray with short array returns zero
fromArray with short array returns identity
